USER EXPERIENCE RESEARCH MUTUAL NON-DISCLOSURE AGREEMENT (“NDA”)

‌

D’Well Informatics and Services Pvt Ltd, whose principal place of business is H-10, Kasthurba Nagar, Kadavanthra, Kochi -682020, Kerala. (“D’Well”) and the other party identified below (“You”) agree this NDA as follows

‌

1.You agree to take part in a study under this NDA (the“Study”) for the purpose of assisting D’Well in researching and analysing the usability of its current and proposed products and services (the “Purpose”). This NDA comes into effect on the date you sign this NDA , as set out below.

‌

2.In the course of Your participation in the Study , You may be requested to provide comments, feedback ideas, reports, suggestions data or other information to D’Well (collectively "Feedback"). You agree that your voice and/or image may be recorded and such recording will also be considered "Feedback" . You agree that D’Well may use any Feedback You provide to develop and enhances client’s current or future products and services. You agree that you will not disclose to D’Well any third-party information that you are otherwise obligated to maintain as confidential .


3.Any feedback You communicate to D’Well as being confidential in writing and any information provided to You by D’Well and clients during the Study period shall be considered confidential ("Confidential information") .

‌

4.A party receiving Confidential Information under this NDA (the "Receiver") may only use Confidential information for the Study and/or the Purpose . Receiver shall protect Confidential Information and prevent any unauthorised use or disclosure of Confidential Information .You shall not share any Confidential Information with any third-party , D’Well may only share Confidential Information with its clients, group companies , employees , agents or third party contractors (or those of its group companies) ("Personnel who need to know it in connection with the purpose. D’Well shall ensure that its Personnel keep the Confidential Information confidential and only use it for the purpose. D’Well will not disclose Your personal Information without your consent, Except as otherwise provided by this NDA any personal information collected by D’Well during the study shall be used by D’Well in accordance with D’Well’s general privacy policy.

‌

5. Confidential Information does not include information that .(a) was known to receive without restriction before receipt from discloser (b) is publicly available through no fault of receiver (c) is lawfully received by receiver from a third party without a duty of confidentiality ; or (d)is independently develop by receiver . A party may disclose Confidential Information when compelled to do so by law provided that it gives reasonable prior notice to the other party unless a court orders that such notice is forbidden.

‌

6.Either party may terminate this NDA on thirty days prior written notice , but this NDA's provisions will still survive in respect of Confidential Information disclosed before termination


7.Unless the parties otherwise agree in writing receiver's duty to protect Confidential Information expire five years from disclosure

‌

8.This NDA imposes no obligation to proceed with any arrangement.

‌

9.This NDA imposes no obligation on D’Well to use Your Feedback , With exception of the limited rights necessary for D’Well to use the Confidential Information for the purpose , neither party acquires any intellectual property rights under this NDA

‌

10.This NDA does not create agency or partnership relationship. No person other than You, D’Well and D’Well's group companies have any rights under this NDA. This NDA is not assignable or transferable by either party without the prior written consent of the other party

‌

11.This NDA is the parties entire agreement on this topic, superseding any other agreements . Any amendments must be in writing .Failure to enforce any of the provisions of this NDA will not constitute a waiver.

‌

12.This NDA and all disputes and claims arising out of or in connection with it are governed by INDIAN law. With the sole exception of any application for injunctive relief , the parties irrevocably submit to the exclusive jurisdiction of the Delhi courts .
